description: Provides students with basic personal and interpersonal leadership skills that can be used within and outside of a work setting. Through practice, the leadership experience helps students explore motivation, decision-making, time management, power, team building, conflict, ethics, dealing with change, communication skills, and diversity issues.

Trains new ambassadors to lead campus and housing tours. Creates educated, ethically and morally responsible, fully confident TOUR (Team of Undergraduate Recruiters) Ambassadors who are engaged, reflective, creative, and caring members of their communities who can contribute to the success of prospective and new students.
